  <h2 class="subhead">Check Yourself</h2>
  <p>What does the standard deviation tell us?</p>
  <div class="reveal1" style="margin-left: 35px;">
    <p>&#x203A; <span style="color: #680a12; text-decoration: underline; cursor: pointer;"><em>View/hide answer</em></span></p>
  </div>
  <div class="toggle1" style="margin-left: 35px;">
    <p>It is a distance which describes the range +/- from the mean containing a particular fraction of the  values; it describes the shape of the bell curve.</p>
    <p>&#xA0;</p>
  </div>
  <p>What is variance?</p>
  <div class="reveal2" style="margin-left: 35px;">
    <p>&#x203A; <span style="color: #680a12; text-decoration: underline; cursor: pointer;"><em>View/hide answer</em></span></p>
  </div>
  <div class="toggle2" style="margin-left: 35px;">
    <p>A measure of how much spread there is in the possible different outcomes.</p>
    <p>&#xA0;</p>
  </div>
  <p>What is the coefficient of variation?</p>
  <div class="reveal3" style="margin-left: 35px;">
    <p>&#x203A; <span style="color: #680a12; text-decoration: underline; cursor: pointer;"><em>View/hide answer</em></span></p>
  </div>
  <div class="toggle3" style="margin-left: 35px;">
    <p>The standard deviation divided by the mean. If it's less than 1, the distribution is considered low-variance.</p>
    <p>&#xA0;</p>
  </div>
